---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SimplePromptTool from '../components/SimplePromptTool';
import { generatePromptMaker } from '../utils/promptTransformers';

Astro.response.headers.set('Cache-Control', 's-maxage=300, stale-while-revalidate=3600');
---
<Layout
  title="Prompt Maker — Free AI Prompt Builder for ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini & More"
  description="Free prompt maker that converts plain language into structured AI prompts — with role framing, task clarity, output format, and tone. Works with ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, and every major model. No sign-up."
>
  <div id="root">
    <SimplePromptTool
      client:only="react"
      seoTitle="Prompt Maker"
      seoDescription="Describe your task and get a structured, ready-to-use AI prompt in seconds."
      inputPlaceholder="Describe what you want to build a prompt for... e.g. write a product launch email for a SaaS tool targeting startup founders"
      buttonLabel="Build Prompt"
      transform={generatePromptMaker}
    />
  </div>

  <div class="px-6 py-12 space-y-6">
    <div class="text-center space-y-3 py-4">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-[#1a1a1a]">Prompt Maker</h1>
      <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-base max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        A prompt maker takes your plain-language description and builds a structured, expert-level prompt — with role framing, task clarity, output format, and tone baked in. This AI prompt builder works with ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Midjourney, and every major model. Free, no sign-up required.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-xl p-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] mb-3">What is a prompt maker?</h2>
      <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
        A prompt maker is a free tool that converts a plain-language description into a structured AI prompt. It adds role framing, task clarity, output format, and tone — giving any AI model exactly what it needs to respond precisely.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Most people type raw questions into ChatGPT or Claude and get generic, padded responses. A prompt maker fixes that by restructuring your intent into the format AI models actually follow. Writers use it for emails and copy. Developers use it as an OpenAI prompt builder for GPT-4o API system prompts. Analysts use it for research synthesis. The common thread: every use case benefits from structured input.
      </p>
      <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Here's what this prompt builder adds to every input:
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
      <div class="border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] mb-4">What This Prompt Builder Adds to Your Input</h2>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-lg">&#127917;</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm">Role &amp; persona</p>
              <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs mt-0.5">Assigns the AI an expert role before the task begins — the single highest-impact addition to any prompt</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-lg">&#129513;</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm">Task clarity</p>
              <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs mt-0.5">Defines the exact goal, scope, and constraints so the model knows where to stop and what to prioritize</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-lg">&#128203;</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm">Output format</p>
              <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs mt-0.5">Specifies structure — list, paragraph, table, code — so responses are immediately usable without reformatting</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="mt-0.5 text-lg">&#127919;</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm">Tone &amp; audience</p>
              <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs mt-0.5">Sets the voice and identifies who the output is written for — critical for emails, marketing, and documentation</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-xl p-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] mb-3">Works as an OpenAI Prompt Builder</h2>
        <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3">
          This tool doubles as an OpenAI prompt builder for GPT-4o, ChatGPT-5, and the OpenAI API. The structured output maps directly to the <code class="bg-[#fdf6e3] px-1 rounded text-xs">system</code> and <code class="bg-[#fdf6e3] px-1 rounded text-xs">user</code> message fields in the API — paste the role and instructions into your system prompt, and the task into the user message. No restructuring needed.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-full text-xs font-medium text-[#1a1a1a]">GPT-4o</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-full text-xs font-medium text-[#1a1a1a]">ChatGPT-5</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-full text-xs font-medium text-[#1a1a1a]">Claude</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-full text-xs font-medium text-[#1a1a1a]">Gemini</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-full text-xs font-medium text-[#1a1a1a]">Grok</span>
          <span class="px-3 py-1 bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-full text-xs font-medium text-[#1a1a1a]">OpenAI API</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-xl p-6 space-y-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1a1a1a]">Prompt Makers for Every AI Model</h2>
      <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Different models respond best to differently structured prompts. Use the model-specific version for best results:
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <a href="/chatgpt-prompt-generator" class="block bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-xl p-4 hover:bg-[#f0e8d0] transition-colors">
          <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm mb-1">ChatGPT prompt maker</p>
          <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs">Structured prompts for GPT-4o and ChatGPT-5</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/claude-prompt-generator" class="block bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-xl p-4 hover:bg-[#f0e8d0] transition-colors">
          <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm mb-1">Claude prompt maker</p>
          <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs">XML-tagged prompts with system prompt structure</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/gemini-prompt-generator" class="block bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-xl p-4 hover:bg-[#f0e8d0] transition-colors">
          <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm mb-1">Gemini prompt maker</p>
          <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs">Numbered-section format for Gemini 2.0 and Ultra</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/" class="block bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-xl p-4 hover:bg-[#f0e8d0] transition-colors">
          <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm mb-1">Midjourney prompt builder</p>
          <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs">Visual art prompts with style, lighting, and camera</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/grok-prompt-generator" class="block bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-xl p-4 hover:bg-[#f0e8d0] transition-colors">
          <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm mb-1">Grok prompt maker</p>
          <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs">Directness calibration and spicy mode framing</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/chatgpt-image-prompt-generator" class="block bg-[#fdf6e3] border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-xl p-4 hover:bg-[#f0e8d0] transition-colors">
          <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm mb-1">Image prompt maker</p>
          <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs">DALL-E and image generation prompts</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="border border-[#c8c0a8] rounded-xl p-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="space-y-5">
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm">What is a prompt maker?</p>
          <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs mt-1">A prompt maker is a free tool that converts a plain-language task description into a structured AI prompt — adding role framing, output format, and tone automatically so you get better results from any AI model without writing the structure yourself.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm">Is this prompt maker free?</p>
          <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs mt-1">Yes — completely free with no sign-up, no account, and no generation limits. Describe your task, click "Build Prompt," and get a ready-to-use structured prompt in seconds.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm">What's the difference between a prompt maker and a prompt builder?</p>
          <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs mt-1">Same tool, different search term. Both refer to a tool that takes plain language and outputs a structured AI prompt. "Prompt maker" and "prompt builder" are used interchangeably — this page covers both.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm">Does this work as a prompt builder for ChatGPT and Claude?</p>
          <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs mt-1">Yes. The output is model-agnostic — structured instructions that work with any AI that follows natural language directions. For model-specific optimizations, use the <a href="/chatgpt-prompt-generator" class="underline hover:no-underline">ChatGPT prompt builder</a> or <a href="/claude-prompt-generator" class="underline hover:no-underline">Claude prompt builder</a>.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <p class="font-semibold text-[#1a1a1a] text-sm">Can I use this as an OpenAI prompt builder for API use?</p>
          <p class="text-[#6b6559] text-xs mt-1">Yes. The generated prompt separates role and instructions from the core task — map the role block into your <code class="bg-[#fdf6e3] px-1 rounded">system</code> message and the task block into your <code class="bg-[#fdf6e3] px-1 rounded">user</code> message in the OpenAI API. Works with GPT-4o, GPT-4o-mini, and the Assistants API. For system prompt tuning and multi-turn conversations, use the ChatGPT-specific builder which adds additional API-compatible structure.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <a href="#root" class="block w-full py-4 bg-[#f0b429] border-2 border-[#1c1c1c] rounded-xl text-center font-bold text-[#1a1a1a] text-lg hover:brightness-95 transition-all">
      Build Your Prompt
    </a>
  </div>
</Layout>
